                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7065.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Nogales</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s December 12 conveyed Obregon last night. He says was already advised
                    of Indian raids and had ordered General Estrada to move troops from Guaymas for
                    strengthening Yaqui River garrisons and that movement is now under way; this
                    will amply protect lives and property in Yaqui Valley. Obregon leaving for south
                    to-day.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
